# Project Odyssey — Planner + Trip Mode Feature Set

Implement a series of interconnected features across the Planner page and Trip Mode page. The planner gets plan activation, configurable day start time, auto commute cards, nearby meal search, expandable trip days, and print support. Trip mode gets a complete overhaul: load the activated plan, geolocation toggle, collapsible map, navigation routing, and removal of mock/broken data.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope**: Features 1 (Planner) and 3 (Destinations tab) are explicitly out of scope per the user's note that a teammate is handling #2 (destinations). However, the user's detailed list covers planner enhancements and trip mode fixes. This plan addresses all items in the user's numbered list.

> [!WARNING]
> **Google Maps API costs**: Commute cards and navigation routing will call the Directions API. The existing `generate-route` endpoint and client-side [Directions](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx#59-130) component already use this API, so no new API keys are needed, but usage will increase.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Active trip persistence**: Currently there is no `status = "active"` distinction in the backend. We will add an `"active"` status value alongside existing `"draft" | "confirmed" | "completed"` to mark which trip is the live one. This means a small backend schema consideration — the `status` column already accepts string values, so no migration is needed.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: Planner Enhancements

---

#### 1.1 — "Activate Plan" Button

##### [MODIFY] [ItinerarySidebar.tsx](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/ItinerarySidebar.tsx)
- Add a new `onActivateTrip?: (id: string) => void` prop
- For each trip card, add an "Activate" button (rocket/play icon) that calls `onActivateTrip`
- Show a green "ACTIVE" badge on the trip with `status === "active"`
- The currently `"active"` badge already shows for the sidebar-selected trip — this is different: "active" means "this is the trip I'll follow in Trip Mode"

##### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (planner2)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx)
- Add `handleActivateTrip(tripId)` — sets trip status to `"active"` via `PUT /api/trips/:id` with `status: "active"`, and sets all other trips back to `"draft"`
- Pass `onActivateTrip={handleActivateTrip}` to [ItinerarySidebar](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/ItinerarySidebar.tsx#21-151)
- Add `"active"` to the `Trip.status` union type

---

#### 1.2 — Configurable Day Start Time

##### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (planner2)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx)
- Add state: `const [dayStartTime, setDayStartTime] = useState("04:00")`
- Update [recalculateDayTimes](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx#369-383) to use `dayStartTime` instead of the hardcoded `"09:00"` default
- Pass `dayStartTime` down to [TimelineView](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/TimelineView.tsx#88-187)

##### [MODIFY] [TimelineView.tsx](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/TimelineView.tsx)
- Accept `startTime?: string` prop (default `"04:00"`)
- Derive `START_HOUR` from the prop instead of hardcoded `4`
- Add a small time-picker in the header bar to allow users to set the day start time

---

#### 1.3 — Auto Commute Cards Between Locations

##### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (planner2)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx)
- Extend [ItineraryItem](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx#37-52) type with: `isCommute?: boolean`, `commuteMode?: "transit" | "driving"`, `commuteDurationMin?: number`
- Create `insertCommutes(items: ItineraryItem[]): ItineraryItem[]` — loops through items, inserts a commute card between each pair of non-break items that have lat/lng
- Modify [recalculateDayTimes](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx#369-383) to treat commute items specially (their duration is the travel time)
- On schedule change, auto-call `insertCommutes` then [recalculateDayTimes](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx#369-383)

##### [MODIFY] [TimelineView.tsx](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/TimelineView.tsx)
- Render commute cards with a distinct dashed-border + car/bus icon style
- Commute cards get a transport mode selector (toggle between 🚗 Car and 🚌 Transit)
- Commute cards are not draggable/sortable — they auto-position between activities

