#### 1.4 — Meal Break with Nearby Restaurant Search

##### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (planner2)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx)
- Update [handleAddMealBreak(day, afterIndex?)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/page.tsx#849-866) to accept an optional parameter for *which* item the break goes after
- When the user clicks "Add Meal Break" on a timeline item, use the preceding item's lat/lng to call `POST /api/map/search-places` with query `"restaurants near {lat},{lng}"`
- Show a small dropdown/modal of nearby results, let the user pick one, and insert it as the meal break location with real placeId + coordinates

##### [MODIFY] [TimelineView.tsx](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/planner2/components/TimelineView.tsx)
- Add a "🍽️+" button on each activity card that triggers meal break insertion *after* that item
- When clicked, show a loading state then a mini search results panel inline

