#### 2.4 — Map Shows Navigation Route to Next Location

##### [MODIFY] [page.tsx (trip)](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/trip/page.tsx)
- Determine the "next" location: the first un-checked-out item that has coordinates
- Pass a `routeItems` prop to [MapComponent](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx#181-266) containing just [current/user location, next location] for focused navigation
- The existing [Directions](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx#59-130) component in [MapComponent](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx#181-266) already renders routes via Google Directions API — we just need to feed it the right 2-point items

##### [MODIFY] [MapComponent.tsx](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx)
- Add optional `routeToNext?: { origin: { lat: number; lng: number }; destination: { lat: number; lng: number; name: string } }` prop
- When provided, the [Directions](file:///Users/sadmanshaharier/Documents/ProjectOdyssey/client/odyssey/app/components/MapComponent.tsx#59-130) component uses this 2-point route instead of the full day's items
- Add a "Full Route / Next Only" toggle on the map

