## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
Since this is a frontend-heavy change set, the primary verification will be done through browser-based testing:

1. **Planner Page (`/planner2`)**:
   - Verify "Activate" button appears on sidebar trip cards
   - Activate a trip, check the badge changes
   - Navigate to Trip Mode, verify the activated trip loads
   - Add/remove days using +/- buttons, verify schedule persistence
   - Drag items and verify commute cards appear between activities
   - Add a meal break after an item, verify restaurant search appears
   - Click Print, verify clean layout opens

2. **Trip Mode Page (`/trip`)**:
   - Verify the active trip loads (not just the latest)
   - Toggle geolocation on/off, check that auto-detection responds
   - Toggle map open/close on both mobile and desktop viewports
   - Verify the map shows route to the next unvisited location
   - Check In / Check Out items without placeId — verify no errors
   - Navigate to items with coordinates but no placeId — verify Google Maps opens correctly

### Manual Verification
- The user should verify on their running dev servers (already running on ports 3000/4000)
- Walk through each feature in sequence on `/planner2` then `/trip`
- Test with real trip data and verify backend persistence via the Network tab
